==English==

===Etymology===
As a Scandinavian name: Literal translation from [[Old Norse]] as Son of God, or Son of Chief, the meanings having same translation; both obviously male in form.

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɪm|-ɪm]]

===Proper noun===
'''Kim'''

# A male [[given name]].
# A female given name, a short form of [[Kimberly]].
# A [[surname]] very common in [[Korea]].

